  "prompt": "Can I wear solid colors over camo?",
  "response": "Yes, you can definitely wear solid colors over camouflage. Camouflage patterns typically feature a blend of natural tones, so pairing them with solid colors can help create a balanced look. When choosing your solid colors, consider those that complement the colors in the camo pattern. Neutral colors like black, white, gray, or beige often work well, but you can also opt for bolder colors if you want to add a vibrant contrast. Just make sure the solid color doesn't clash with the camo pattern and that the overall outfit feels cohesive.",
